{{Music of Ivory Coast}}

'''Abissa''' is a cultural concept embracing the music, dance and spiritual life of the [[Nzema people|Nzema]] <!-- This was a redlink to N’zima—if these aren't the same, change it back --> people in the town of [[Grand-Bassam]], [[Côte d'Ivoire]], [[West Africa]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1995/11/03/world/grand-bassam-journal-in-one-unbridled-week-a-town-s-moment-of-truth.html|title=Grand-Bassam Journal; In One Unbridled Week, a Town's Moment of Truth|first=Howard W.|last=French|date=November 3, 1995|work=New York Times|accessdate=22 August 2009}}</ref> The best-known expression of Abissa is a festival celebrated in the last week of October. It is a time of forgiveness and rebirth marked by a week-long celebration.
[[File:Abissa 2016 3.jpg|thumb|Women dancing at Abissa 2016]]

